    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@jreback idxmin/idxmax return label whereas argmin/argmax return location. I think this was the main reason why Wes did not want to override. Since override is not done, both exist - at least on Series, same names idxmin/idxmax are kept on DataFrame. \n\n``` python\nIn [33]: s = pd.Series([10, 30, 20], list('abc'))\n\nIn [34]: s\nOut[34]:\na    10\nb    30\nc    20\n\nIn [35]: s.idxmax()\nOut[35]: 'b'\n\nIn [36]: s.argmax()\nOut[36]: 1\n```\n"
  },
